<HEAD>British Businessman Robert Maxwell to Invest in Argentina</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British media mogul Robert
Maxwell plans to invest up to $200 million in Argentina in the
communications and forestry industries, local news agencies
reported.
   ``The differences between Great Britain and Argentina have gone
too far. The moment has arrived to return to our traditional
friendship,'' Maxwell told reporters at a Friday news conference
