war in 1982 over the Falkland Islands in the South Atlantic, said
they would upgrade diplomatic relations to the consular level and
remove trade and travel restrictions in effect for nearly six years.
   Menem said Maxwell, who owns a string of newspapers including a
leading British tabloid, the Daily Mirror, ``is thinking about an
initial investment of $150 million to $200 million.''
