<FIRST>r a PM-CamperShooting     10-21 0342</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Camper Shooting,0350</SECOND>
<HEAD>Englishman Shot by Police Chief After Month Alone in Wilderness</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OROVILLE, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former computer analyst who returned
from a month alone in the wilderness with ``a wild look in his
eye'' was shot and killed after pointing a gun at the police chief,
authorities said.
   David Brian Peatroy, 34, died Thursday as seven or eight people
looked on after he pointed a loaded 9mm pistol at Police Chief Al
Rise and threatened to kill him, Rise and witnesses said.
   Rise had responded to reports of a man brandishing a gun on Main
Street in this town about eight miles south of the Canadian border.
   ``He pointed (the gun) right in my face. ... I had no other
choice,'' Rise said. ``It was over in five seconds. He was
definitely crazy _ stark, raving crazy. He had a wild look in his
eye when he turned around and looked at me.''
   Witnesses said Peatroy, a resident alien originally from
Worthing, England, began acting erratically Tuesday, a week after
returning from a month alone in the Pasayten Wilderness of
Washington's North Cascades mountains.
   He had come to the Oroville area just a few days before leaving
for the wilderness, said Okanogan County Sheriff Jim Weed, whose
department is investigating the shooting in this town of 1,500
people. Peatroy had worked for several years as a computer analyst
in San Diego.
   Pat Miller, co-owner of an outfitting company in nearby
Winthrop, said she and her husband, Claude, had helped Peatroy pack
supplies Sept. 10 to an old tungsten mine in the North Cascades.
   ``He just wanted to get into the wilderness and stay, get away
from the hustle and bustle of city life,'' Mrs. Miller said. ``I
thought he was a nice boy.''
   But Peatroy returned Oct. 10 a changed man, she said.
   ``He was like hyper once in a while,'' Mrs. Miller said. ``His
laugh was a little hysterical, but he'd been in the hills for 30
days and was talking like a magpie, as anybody would.''
</TEXT>
