<SECOND>PM-BRF--Hummer Sale,0198</SECOND>
<HEAD>LTV May Sell Hummer Military Vehicle To Public</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For motorists seeking something special in
off-road adventure, a defense contractor thinks it may have the
answer.
   The builder of the Hummer military vehicle may soon make the
four-wheel-drive, five-ton jeep-like vehicle available to the
public.
   LTV Corp.'s AM General Division, which builds the Hummer, or
High-Mobility Multi-Purpose Wheeled Vehicle, has developed a new
version with a heavier chassis that can carry 2\ tons of cargo.
   The Hummer is being sold to the Army, but AM General has
received inquiries from individuals who want the vehicle for
hunting, ranching or just plain off-road fun.
   Craig Mac Nab, company spokesman, said the South Bend,
Ind.-based division is weighing product liability questions and
conducting market studies on demand for the Hummer, which could
cost around $30,000 each.
   Mac Nab told The Dallas Morning News he believes the vehicle
could be competitively priced with other upper-end, off-road
vehicles.
   ``It wouldn't have to be as expensive as a military model
because you wouldn't need all those features,'' Mac Nab said.
Military versions sport such features as armor plating and Stinger
missile carriers.
