<HEAD>Two Fires in Channel Tunnel Injure Nine Workers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DOVER, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two fires broke out in the tunnel being
constructed under the English Channel, and nine construction
workers suffered smoke inhalation, the Fire Brigade said Saturday.
   Both small fires started in locomotives being used to haul
construction materials.
   In the first fire, late Friday, three construction workers
suffered smoke inhalation. The second fire early Saturday, about
five hours later, left six workers suffering from smoke inhalation,
the Kent Fire Brigade said.
   Both fires were extinguished by construction workers, and the
injured were treated at a nearby medical center.
   The 34-mile-long tunnel will consist of two one-way rail tunnels
and a smaller service tunnel between them. It is being dug
simultaneously from England and France under the English Channel
and is scheduled to open in May 1993.
