<FIRST>r i AM-Israel     10-21 0318</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Israel,0328</SECOND>
<HEAD>Palestinians Hold General Strike; Two Die Of Wounds</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SERGEI SHARGORODSKY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Palestinians in the occupied territories held a
general strike Saturday to press demands for independence and
clashed with Israeli troops, leaving at least 11 Arabs wounded,
Arab reports said.
   The army said two Palestinian youths died overnight of wounds
suffered in earlier clashes. The deaths raised to 598 the number of
Palestinians killed by Israeli soldiers or civilians in the
uprising. Forty Israelis have died.
   Traffic throughout the occupied West Bank and Gaza Strip came to
a halt and shops and businesses were closed following strike calls
from the underground leadership of the 22-month-old Palestinian
revolt.
   The uprising leaders said in a leaflet that Saturday's strike
was meant to show rejection of Israel's peace plan and to press
demands for an independent Palestinian state.
   Israel's plan calls for elections in the occupied territories to
choose Palestinian representatives for negotiations on a limited
autonomy.
   The PLO has rejected the proposal.
   Demonstrations erupted Saturday in Nablus, the largest town in
the West Bank, and the neighboring Balata refugee camp. Arab
hospital officials in Nablus said they treated five people shot by
Israeli troops.
   Scattered clashes were also reported in the occupied Gaza Strip,
and hospital officials said they treated six wounded. The military
command said it was checking the reports.
   At least 132 Palestinians have been killed by fellow Arabs on
suspicion of collaborating with Israeli authorities.
   The army command said a 17-year-old youth from Khan Yunis died
at an Israeli hospital late Friday. It said the youth, identified
by Arab reporters as Iyad El-Asi, was shot by troops Friday when he
tried to grab a rifle from a soldier.
   At the Tel Hashomer hospital in Israel, 18-year-old Nidal Hajaij
of Gaza City died of a head wound suffered in a clash with soldiers
earlier this month, the army said.
</TEXT>
