<HEAD>Turkey Accuses Syria of Downing Turkish Plane</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Foreign Ministry accused Syria of
downing a Turkish airplane on a geographical survey mission
Saturday, killing all five crew members.
   Ministry spokesman Murat Sungar said a propeller plane of the
Turkish Title Deeds Office was shot down Saturday morning by two
Syrian MiG-21s that violated Turkish air space. He said all five
