<HEAD>Tennessee Congressman's Wife Arrested for Driving with Expired License</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rep. Harold Ford, D-Tenn., paid $50 bail to
release his wife from jail in the District of Columbia Saturday
after she was arrested for driving with an expired license, police
officials said.
   Dorothy Ford was stopped after she allegedly ran a red light
near the Capitol building Saturday morning, police said.
   When an officer discovered her driver's license had expired more
than a year ago Mrs. Ford was arrested and taken to a nearby police
