<SECOND>AM-Lottery Jackpot,0122</SECOND>
<HEAD>One Ticket Wins Record $37 Lottery Million Prize</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRAINTREE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Officials at the state lottery played a
waiting game Saturday but no one came forward to claim a $37
million jackpot, the largest in the state lottery's history.
   Just one ticket, sold at Barcelo's Market in Methuen, bears the
lucky numbers drawn Friday in the Mass Millions game:
10-15-25-28-31-34. Methuen is about 25 miles north of Boston near
the New Hampshire line.
   It was the largest jackpot since Massachusetts began running
state lotteries in 1972 and attracted more than $18 million in
wagers for Friday night's drawing.
   The largest U.S. lottery won by a single ticket was a $55.15
million jackpot in Florida last year.
